taphysis\nDiaphysis\nEpiphysis\n4. Fracture displacement: Fracture displacement describes what has happened to the\nbone during the fracture. In general, when describing a fracture, the body is assumed\nto be in the anatomic position and the injury is then described in terms of the distal\ncomponent displacement in\nrelation to the proximal\ncomponent.\nDisplacement can include one\nor more of:\n• Angulation\n• Translation\n• Rotation\n• distraction or impaction\n18"}